<paragraph id="AC4984F9A7493458C82863948DFF465C" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
First recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="9B649D50D8959D144AA18387A98E5486" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri (1980)</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of four females collected in June and August 1974-1977. It occurs in southern Europe, most notably Sicily and Malta; throughout North Africa, Egypt and also in Israel (
<bibRefCitation id="E0F9981296453C86E2AF81DF390270B2" author="Gusenleitner, J" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" refId="B11" refString="Gusenleitner, J, 1998a. Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 9. Die Gattung Pseudepipona SAUSSURE. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30/2: 487-495." title="Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 9. Die Gattung Pseudepipona SAUSSURE. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30 / 2: 487 - 495." year="1998 a">Gusenleitner 1998a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
